{{Infobox language |name = Jirajara |nativename = Hirahara |region = [[Falcón]] |states = [[Venezuela]] |extinct = early 20th century |familycolor = American |fam1 = [[Jirajaran languages]] |iso3 = none |linglist = qfg |glotto=jira1235 |glottoname=Jirajaran }}
'''Jirajara''' is an extinct language of western [[Venezuela]]. Other than being part of the [[Jirajaran languages|Jirajaran family]], its classification is uncertain due to a lack of data. See [[Jirajaran languages]] for details.
